{"word":"στρατιῶτις","slug":"στρατιῶτις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στρατιῶτις</b></el> <el>(στρᾰτιῶτις, ιδος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <a href='S:στρατιώτης'><el>στρατιώτης</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>, <el>στρ. ἀρωγά</el> <i>the martial</i> aid, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>στρ.</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>ναῦς</el>), <i>a troop-ship, transport</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}